{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01C3PaNfX3AauRH4bKsDkJ2i","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Analyzing the two peptides:\n\n**PEP-F9A8AC8ACB**: `RQKGLQGRLYRLLQGSGNHAAGILT(Nle)-NH2`\n- Designed analogue retaining the C-terminal orexin pharmacophore `...HAAGILT(Nle)-NH2`\n- Nle (norleucine) is a conservative, oxidation-resistant isostere of Met — preserves potency\n- All L-amino acids; charge distribution intact\n\n**PEP-1644F77D58**: `RSGPPGLQGRLQ(D-Citrulline)LLQASGNHAAGILTM-NH2`\n- Native orexin-B sequence (`RSGPPGLQGRLQRLLQASGNHAAGILTM-NH2`) with **R12 → D-Citrulline**\n- This single position carries two destabilizing modifications simultaneously:\n  1. **D-stereochemistry** at a backbone position critical for receptor engagement\n  2. **Loss of the conserved cationic guanidinium** (Arg → neutral citrulline) at a residue known to be important for orexin receptor binding\n- Combined D-config + charge ablation at a key pharmacophore residue typically causes large potency losses (often >10-fold) at OX2R\n\nThe orexin C-terminal \"message\" segment (`HAAGILTM/L-NH2`) is preserved in both, but PEP-1644F77D58's mid-helix R→D-Cit substitution disrupts the receptor-engaging address region. PEP-F9A8AC8ACB has only a conservative Nle-for-Met swap.\n\nPrediction: **PEP-F9A8AC8ACB** is more potent (lower EC50) at OX2R."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":528,"cache_read_input_tokens":25707,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":528},"output_tokens":49,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d39fe5fc-8af1-488d-b23c-c7c884c0f943","uuid":"876d4c7f-f942-40b6-8b5d-3bbc68544a25"}
